 NVIDIA GPU Architecture group is looking for architects and software developers to join our various architecture efforts. A key part of NVIDIA's strength is to innovate in the graphics and parallel computing fields, delivering the highest performance in the world for graphics processing. We are constantly looking for ways to improve our GPU architecture and maintain our leadership.
 What youâ€™ll be doing:
 In this position, you will be working with other world-class architects on analysis, validation, and tuning of graphics architectures and features that advance the state of art in performance and efficiency.
 Developing and enhancing innovative tools for architectural performance analysis
 Performance analysis of graphics hardware features and APIs, leading to recommendations for future architectures
 Deriving algorithms for tuning of games on existing hardware, possible prototyping of implementations
 What we need to see:
 Bachelors or Masters Degree in a relevant field (Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering or ECE) or equivalent experience
 5-10 years meaningful experience in real-time 3D rendering or ray tracing, knowledge of DirectX or OpenGL preferred.
 Strong programming ability in C and C++. Python scripting a big plus.
 Proven background in mathematics, algorithms and data structures required, additional background in Compute Graphics preferred
 A great teammate; results-oriented with a positive attitude.
